channel.title: Plants of Jollys Road, Anakie
channel.description: This collection contains records of plant species observed from along Jollys Road in Anakie, including the roadside and the 18-hectare Trust for Nature covenanted property of 25 Jollys Road.

item.title: Polycarpon tetraphyllum
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.description: An occasional weed of disturbed, often gravelly areas.

item.title: Pterostylis smaragdyna
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.description: Many tens of plants both flowering and sterile. Higher density than observed in past.

item.title: Chrysanthemoides monilifera subsp. monilifera
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.description: Cluster of seedlings arising from fox scat containing almost solely the seed of Boneseed.

item.title: Olearia pannosa subsp. cardiophylla
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.description: Severely browsed by wallabies. One of only two plants of this species found in the near vicinity. The plant was caged to protect from Wallaby browsing. The other plant is also caged and approximately 30 metres away.

item.title: Olearia pannosa subsp. cardiophylla
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.description: One of only two plants of this species found in the near vicinity. The plant was caged to protect from Wallaby browsing. The other plant is also caged and approximately 30 metres away.

item.title: Clematis decipiens
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Flammuliform leaf is the key feature for C. decipiens. C. microphylla s.s. is trifoliolate, having 3 sets of usually 3 leaflets with a total of 9-11 leaflets per leaf. ID confirmed by Neville Walsh.

item.title: Isolepis spp.
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Maybe Isolepis cernua subsp. platycarpus. ID by Neville Walsh.

item.title: Pterostylis sp. aff. revoluta (Inland)
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.description: Large Autumn Greenhood. Woodland/Open Forest habitat.

item.title: Senecio pinnatifolius var. lanceolatus
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.description: A seedling that recruited following the Jan 2006 wildfire.

item.title: Lobelia gibbosa sensu Walsh Albrecht & Knox (2010)
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.category: id~Lobelia gibbosa sensu Walsh Albrecht & Knox (2010)

item.title: Papilio aegeus aegeus
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.description: The female Orchard Swallowtail adult butterfly that visited Jollys Road in summer 2011 must have laid an egg. This observation was made on the same lemon tree where the butterfly was observed.
